This paper deals with resource allocation strategies for a wireless-powered multiantenna multicasting system, which involves communication, networking, and information theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), followed by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.GT (Game Theory).
